				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, kids...
<br />

<br />
First of all, the "grand idea" of this thread was to give meaning to the whole idea of "caught spies". So next time you post, keep that in mind...
<br />
(this just to remind the authors of last two posts)
<br />
 
<br />
As a response to last two posts: 
<br />

<br />
My idea was never to give players the right to determine the amount of ransom as I said it should be determined progressively not by player but by computer !
<br />

<br />
Maybe I didn`t make my idea clear so, here I go again, my idea with some improvements:
<br />

<br />
Player A uses spy function General Information Gathering to player B. Player A:s spy attack is a failure and spy get`s caught by player B, who now asks for ransom for player A:s caught spy.
<br />

<br />
NOTE: This all is done by the "almighty" computer and no player involvement is required ie computer calculates the ransom amount and sends a note to player A containing the ransom amount etc. etc. 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Player A must pay the ransom amount 
<br />

<br />
                            OR (now, pay attention kids!)
<br />

<br />
Player A cannot use spy function on player B, before ransom has been payed OR certain amount of time has passed(for example 1-2 hours). 
<br />

<br />
Player A can however use his spy attack on other players he doesn`t have ransom-letters from!
<br />

<br />
In my opinion spy "functions" should be divided into three categories:
<br />
(These are just EXAMPLES)
<br />
 
<br />
 1.
<br />
  General Information Gathering 
<br />
  Detailed Information Gathering 
<br />
  Steal Secret Info
<br />
  Steal Common Technology
<br />
  Steal Important Technology 
<br />

<br />
  2.
<br />
  Computer Virus Infiltration 
<br />
  Devastating Network Worm 
<br />
  Sabotage 
<br />
  Incite Riot 
<br />
  Artificial Disease 
<br />
  Red death 
<br />
  Assassination 
<br />

<br />
  3.
<br />
  
<br />
  Strike Base 
<br />
  Meteor Strike 
<br />
  EMP Storm 
<br />
  Stellar Bombardment 
<br />
  
<br />
So, when you use spy "function" from cat. 1 unsuccesfully(spy gets caught), then the ransom letter comes in and applies to that category!
<br />
Again if you use, for example, Sabotage from cat.2 then cat.2 would be unavailable until ransom paid or certain time has passed. Simple, eh!
<br />

<br />
The operations in first and second category would be done by a spy and the third category would contain operations that couldn`t be done by a single spy and therefore would be out of the whole ransom-idea. This simply for the reality part of the game.
<br />

<br />
I am suggesting the time-limit on the ransom-letter and that would describe the time needed to send a replacement-spy in case ransom amount is not payed.(this again for the sake of "reality")
<br />

<br />
__________________________________________________________
<br />
I hope that was clear enough for everyone, but feel free to correct and point out mistakes/irregularities(it`s 3:00 am, while writing this!!!)<br />_________________<br />"Ia! Ia! Cthulhu fhtagn!"</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
