				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The only problem with your idea is that you couldn't have the randsom based on the caught spies power, but rather on the power of the person who caught it. why? because it would be too abusable:
<br />

<br />
Example
<br />
I am 650k in power, so say the formula works it out and that means a $20 000 000PP randsom per spy i have caught...now, i have a friend who has just joined archspace and is broke...So I get him to set his detection very high and send a few spies at him, so that each time i have to pay him the cash..i don't need the cash so much, he needs it badly, he has a huge advantage....
<br />

<br />
thus, you would need to set the cost of the spy random based on the power of the person accepting it...makes sense also if you consider that someone who only makes, say $30 000 a year would be very happy to get a $1 million randsom, while someone who makes $1 million a year would be offended and would probably demand a $10 mil ransom etc<br />_________________<br />Houston
<br />
a.k.a Son of Sam
<br />
------------------
<br />
Canadian Right
<br />
Holiday Camp</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
