				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well perhaps we can do it like this:
<br />

<br />
If a spy gets caught the player that was spyed upon can do the following things.
<br />
- Make an example out of him (so in sence killing him) now what does this do it scares the spys of the player that send them and prevents spying for 24 hours or something like that.
<br />
- Convert him. You try to pursuade him that your a better lord than the one that send the spy. This will cost cash (pesuading = expensive) and will give you a +... Spy CM against the player that send him (representing info the spy gave)
<br />
- Interrogate him. You get some usefull bit of info out of him (some bit of info lets say a list of useless info's like whats on planet X and usefuller info like planet number or what is in the ship pool)
<br />
- Randsom him. Ask cash from the player that send the spy. Now if there will be no character spy's why would someone accept this? well a CM decrease + since you the guy that send the spy let someone of your people die well honour isnt in there If there are spy characters well a good caracter is worth saving
<br />

<br />
Now since spy's have 2 probs. 1 No real use 2 no characters these ideas are pretty much useless since nearly no one will use these functions but lets say we add spy characters and make new missions like sabotage (destroying a building on a planet and depending on building type you could decrease CM like research = 1 less research CM for a while showing scared scientists + increased guard = bad work eviroment)
<br />
Assasinate. Try to kill a commander in the pool but verry verry hard (this should make spy's suddenly more dangerous) Sabotage fleet. Cause some damage so peeps need to repair the fleet or if the sabotage is very succesfull the player wont notice but once in battle the fleet will like lose lifes at start or lose a device)
<br />

<br />
Now these ideas are pretty big so programming will take a while but if there is a goal to work to and to dream of that is already a big something  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> 
